==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sicklebill
<hw>Sic"kle*bill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any one of three species of humming birds of the genus
<gen>Eutoxeres</gen>, native of Central and South America. They have a
long and strongly curved bill. Called also the <altname>sickle-billed
hummer</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A curlew.</def> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>A bird of the genus <gen>Epimachus</gen> and allied
genera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sickled</ent>⟦br⟧
